<section id="command-penreverse">
    <title>PENREVERSE</title>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>PENREVERSE</command>
<command>PX</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Sets the pen's position to DOWN and mode to REVERSE.
In REVERSE mode, the pen draws in a color that is the bitwise negation of whatever pixel is under the pen.
Use <link linkend="command-penpaint">PENPAINT</link> to restore the pen to normal use.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
    <programlisting><userinput>FORWARD 100
PENERASE
BACK 100</userinput></programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</section>
